Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with cryptographic criteria of vectorial Boolean functions and investigates the DLCT property of various special functions. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses the Walsh transform and additive autocorrelation to characterize properties of DLCT, which are tools commonly used in information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the properties of vectorial Boolean functions, which can be viewed as systems with inputs and outputs. 
4. cs.DS (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper uses mathematical tools such as the Walsh transform and additive autocorrelation to investigate the DLCT property of vectorial Boolean functions. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper deals with the complexity of vectorial Boolean functions and investigates their cryptographic properties.
